Smoky Avocado Toast with Miso (The Best!)

   This avocado toast recipe is truly the best. But before I get into it,
   let me tell you how it came about.

   I don‚Äôt know if I ever told you, but I am a huge bibliophile.

   Yep, I have a deep love for books. I love to read them and I love to
   look at them.

   Just yesterday I spent the entire day nose-deep, reading my latest
   Kindle purchase ‚Äì The Hacking Of The American Mind ‚Äì which I highly
   recommend.

   The reason I‚Äôm bringing up books is because, not too long ago, I
   purchased Kintsugi Wellness: The Japanese Art of Nourishing Mind, Body,
   and Spirit by Candice Kumai. It‚Äôs a beautiful book about Japanese
   traditions and practices for cultivating inner strength and living a
   meaningful life. It‚Äôs also packed with yummy recipes, including one I
   fell head over heels in love with:

   Miso avocado toast.

   What can I say other than it‚Äôs the best avocado toast recipe I‚Äôve ever
   tasted!

   It‚Äôs creamy, savory, salty, simple and so delicious! And then one day I
   decided to add my own twist to it‚Ä¶ I sprinkled gochugaru to add
   smokiness and my brain just about exploded.

   Perfection on a plate.

   I‚Äôm not kidding when I say that I crave avocado toast all the time now!

   So without further ado, here‚Äôs my adaptation of Candice‚Äôs amazing miso
   avocado toast recipe.

